&lt;p&gt;Role: Data Management Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are Growers, We are Wholesalers, We are Producers, We Are Budtenders, We are Retailers, We are Partners, and We are Hiring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The Data Management Coordinator supports day-to-day data processes across the organization—making sure data is accurate, organized, and easy to access. This role works cross-functionally to maintain data quality, support reporting, and keep systems running smoothly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate, reliable data that supports daily operations and decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean, consistent data across systems by identifying and resolving discrepancies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep data accessible and up to date so teams can move quickly and efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support reporting and insights that drive operational and strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally (ops, finance, IT, analytics) to collect and maintain key data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring structure to data systems, documentation, and ongoing process improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold data governance, compliance, and security standards across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Strengths&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ year of experience in data management or similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with databases, spreadsheets, and reporting tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with a focus on accuracy and organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to manage multiple priorities and work independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of data quality and governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If we are EMPATHETIC, HONORABLE &amp;amp; ACCOUNTABLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;And we grow ourselves and business with GRIT then we will be&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; CHAMPIONS OF CANNABIS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holistic Industries offers a comprehensive benefits package, including competitive base pay, medical, dental, and vision coverage. We also offer a team member discount in our stores, a Health Savings Account, pet insurance, and a 401(K) with a company match. Additional benefits include company-paid short term and long-term disability, life and AD&amp;amp;D insurance and mental health and urgent care services. Team Members can also take advantage of our referral program and generous paid time off (PTO).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
